# Phase 12 вЂ” Configure Supabase

Create:

```text
lib/supabase/
```

Files:

```text
client.ts
server.ts
middleware.ts
```

> **Breaking change in Next.js 16:** the root-level `middleware.ts` convention has been renamed to **`proxy.ts`**. If you're wiring Supabase session refresh logic into request-level middleware, your project's *root* file must be named `proxy.ts` (the helper file inside `lib/supabase/middleware.ts` can keep its own name вЂ” it's just a regular module, not the Next.js convention file). Using the old `middleware.ts` name at the project root will not run in Next.js 16. Run `npx @next/codemod@latest upgrade` if migrating an existing project, or name the file correctly from the start on a fresh Next.js 16 project.

